description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant Community Paediatrician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There are two posts available, as defined below. Respective job descriptions can be found within the attachments of the advert too. Posts available are as follows:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.0 FTE Consultant Community Paediatrician - ADHD Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.0 FTE Consultant Community Paediatrician - Special Interest (to be agreed)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cambridgeshire Community Services NHS Trust are seeking two substantive Consultants in Community Paediatrics to join a team of experienced Community Paediatricians providing a wide range of Community Paediatric services. One post includes the Lead role for ADHD, the other role has the scope to develop a special interest if in line with service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful post holders will be expected to have broad experience in all aspects of Community Paediatrics and should be competent to assess children in whom abuse and neglect has been suspected. We do not assess children and Young People for sexual abuse.The post holder will be expected to be competent to assess, diagnose, and manage a range neurodevelopmental problems (including ADHD) and disability.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The post holder will be based at the Edwin Lobo Child Development Centre, within the purpose built, Redgrave Children and Young People&#39;s Centre in Luton. You may also be required to travel across Luton &amp; South Bedfordshire to see children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part time applications are also welcome. Please state which post you are applying for by detailing within the first line of the supporting information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To discuss the post, please call Dr C Kearney, Consultant Community Paediatrician and Clinical Lead either via telephone by calling 01582 700300 or email to catherine.kearney@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: Friday 18 December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
